      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "title": "Load Focus First, Then Move Outward",
        "body": "Load the focused graph first. Then load outward by ring: second, third, fourth. Recompute ring membership when focus changes, reuse cached data where possible, and downgrade richer cached content to the new ring cap when needed.",
        "steps": [
          "Load the focused `.node` file first.",
          "Load the second ring before loading farther rings.",
          "Load the third ring after the second ring, and the fourth ring after the third.",
          "Render from whatever valid surface the current ring allows while richer surfaces continue loading in the background.",
          "When focus changes, recompute ring membership and representation caps.",
          "Allow cache to satisfy a ring immediately, but never let cached data exceed the cap of the current ring.",
          "If a richer node or document surface becomes available and the current zoom warrants it, upgrade the rendering in place.",
          "If semantic-zoom-loader is missing where required, show a missing-view error instead of guessing.",
          "Keep the icon contract independent of any one renderer so canvas, DOM, or future renderers can all consume it."
        ],
        "_classBinding": {
